From 7cfaa90d62af709198bea960d7dffe940388ccc9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew Fernandez <matthew.fernandez@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 17:01:11 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Autotools: fix: discover Python, even when not building its
 bindings
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

3153cece5e133ed91181dd179ed263a7e7ecf53a enabled configuring an
alternate path to the Python binary. An unintended side effect of this
change was that builds that disabled the Python bindings
(`--disable-python --disable-python3`) and thus had nothing set in
`$PYTHON3`, tried to run command lines that expanded to “ foo.py” where
foo.py was a non-executable script.

Cc: Michal Suchanek <msuchanek@suse.de>
Gitlab: fixes #2839
Reported-by: Adrian Vovk
---
 CHANGELOG.md | 9 +++++++++
 configure.ac | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md
index d712083411..270c5a0ab9 100644
--- a/CHANGELOG.md
+++ b/CHANGELOG.md
@@ -4,6 +4,14 @@ All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.
 The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
 and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).
 
+## [Unreleased (15.0.1)]
+
+### Fixed
+
+- When building from source from a Git checkout, builds with
+  `--disable-python`/`--disable-python3` once again work. This was a regression
+  in Graphviz 14.1.3. #2839
+
 ## [15.0.0] – 2026-05-23
 
 ### Changed
@@ -3524,6 +3532,7 @@ March 13, 2000: Use AM_PROG_LIBTOOL instead of AC_PROG_LIBTOOL
    in configure.in.  John Ellson <ellson@graphviz.org>
 ```
 
+[Unreleased (15.0.1)]: https://gitlab.com/graphviz/graphviz/compare/15.0.0...main
 [15.0.0]: https://gitlab.com/graphviz/graphviz/compare/14.1.5...15.0.0
 [14.1.5]: https://gitlab.com/graphviz/graphviz/compare/14.1.4...14.1.5
 [14.1.4]: https://gitlab.com/graphviz/graphviz/compare/14.1.3...14.1.4
diff --git a/configure.ac b/configure.ac
index c922d2c45d..a36c805be7 100644
--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -903,6 +903,7 @@ AC_ARG_ENABLE(python3,
   [AS_HELP_STRING([--enable-python3=yes],[python3 language bindings])],
   [], [enable_python3=yes])
 
+AC_CHECK_PROG(PYTHON3,python3,python3)
 if test "$enable_python3" != "yes"; then
   use_python3="No (disabled)"
 else
@@ -912,7 +913,6 @@ else
     if test `$SWIG -help 2>&1 | $EGREP -c '\-python *- Generate'` = 0; then
       use_python="No (swig does not support -python option)"
     else
-      AC_CHECK_PROG(PYTHON3,python3,python3)
       if test "$PYTHON3" = ""; then
         use_python3="No (python3 not available)"
       else
-- 
GitLab
